Pvrchas his Pilgrimes :
Hakluytus posthumus
Purchas his Pilgrimes
Title from engraved title page present in volume 1.
Each of the 4 parts has additional title page with title: Pvrchas his Pilgrimes; and with imprint: London, Printed by William Stansby for Henrie Fetherstone ... 1625.
Continuous pagination & register in vols. 1-2, 3-4.
Old classmark: 694.
Binding: full calf, blind & g. rolled border; spine & board edges g.t., border g.t. on inside covers, raised bands, g. lettering; coloured e.p.; a.e. marbled.

Voyages and travels Early works to 1800. Voyages around the world Early works to 1800. Geography Early works to 1800. Explorers Great Britain. Explorers Spain. Explorers Portugal. Explorers France. Explorers Netherlands.

Haklvytvs posthumus, or, Pvrchas his Pilgrimes : contayning a history of the world, in sea voyages, & lande-trauells / by Englishmen and others, wherein Gods wonders in nature & prouidence, the actes, arts, varieties & vanities of men, w[i]th a world of the worlds rarities are by a world of eyewitnesse-authors related to the world, some left written by Mr. Hakluyt at his death, more since added, his also perused, & perfected, all examined, abreuiated, illustrated w[i]th notes, enlarged w[i]th discourses, adorned w[i]th pictures, and expressed in mapps, in fower parts, each containing fiue bookes ; [compiled] by Samvel Pvrchas, B.D.
4 v ([6] folded leaves of plates) : ill, maps ; 33cm (fol in 6s).
